                           "[The film] traces the history of the atomic bomb from its origins to the present state of global affairs: nine nations possessing
                              nuclear weapons capabilities with others racing to join them, leaving the world held in a delicate balance that could be shattered
                              by an act of terrorism, failed diplomacy, or a simple accident."--Container

