The Greek paradox : promise vs. performance(
                                 Book
                                 )8
                              editions published
                              
                              between
                              1996
                              and
                              1997
                              in 
                              English
                              and held by
                              269 WorldCat member
                              
                              libraries
                              
                              worldwide
                              As a bridge between the East and West, a pole of stability in the Balkans, and a Mediterranean crossroads, Greece could play
                                 a significant role in the post-Cold War world. But Greece's performance in domestic and international policy falls short of
                                 this promise. The essays in The Greek Paradox look at some of the reasons for this gap and suggest possible political and
                                 economic reforms. The contributors shed light on nation-building, political and economic development, modernization, and NATO
                                 and Balkan politics

Nuclear proliferation : risk and responsibility : a report to the Trilateral Commission(
                                 Book
