                           libraries
                           
                           worldwide
                           In October 2001 President George W. Bush received a CIA report that Al Qaeda had smuggled a ten-kiloton nuclear weapon into
                              New York City. It turned out to be a false alarm. The author presents two cases: one that nuclear terrorism is inevitable;
                              the second, that it is preventable

