                              "The authors in this volume agree with these leaders' judgment: nuclear terrorism represents today's gravest national security
                                 challenge. In the pages that follow, fourteen scholars, scientists, and practitioners consider how best to confront and combat
                                 this danger. Their articles address this challenge from all azimuths: from the strategic to tactical, from the ideological
                                 to technical, and from the historical to contemporary"--Page 7

